dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Development. Division of Geology and Topography. Atlas Sheet 32 (1941) New Jersey Geological Survey. Relief shown by 10 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings in feet at low tide. Title is not given. Region covered: southern Burlington County. Original survey 1886, principal features revised, 1903, 1934. Original survey and revisions to 1903 made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer. Revision 1934 by L. P. Plummer, Topographic Engineer. From original surveys and levellings. Based on triangulations of the U.S. Coast and Geodetic Sruvey.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1941.
